# https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Agent> .
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An agent that is driven by the intention to reach a defined objective in driving a process."@en .
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "IntentionalAgent"@en .
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Intentionality is not limited to human agents, but in general to all agents that have the capacity to decide to act in driving a process according to a motivation"@en .
<https://w3id.org/emmo/hume#IntentionalAgent> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "Intentionality will, as of today, normally apply to humans or decision systems designed by humans aimed for reaching a defined objective."@en .
